DEMOBILIZE
  Convert active military in sectors into national reserve.

SYNTAX
  demobilize <sects> <amount> [reserve|civ]
  demo       <sects> <amount> [reserve|civ]

DESCRIPTION
  Transfers military from sector(s) into your national reserve pool
  (or optionally converts them to civilians).  Costs $5 per troop.

  <sects>   - sector(s) to draw from
  <amount>  - how many to demobilize per sector.
              Use a negative number to keep that many and demob rest.
              Example: -10 means "keep 10, demob the rest"
  reserve   - (default) mil becomes nat_reserve
  civ       - mil becomes civilians instead (no reserve gained)

  Requirements:
    - Sector must be >=60% efficient
    - Sector must still be under original ownership (not conquered)
    - You must have enough money ($5/troop)

  The reserve can then be spent via 'enlist' to quickly deploy
  troops anywhere you own.

EXAMPLE
  demobilize 1,-3 100       move 100 mil to reserve, cost $500
  demobilize * -10          keep 10 mil each sector, rest to reserve
  demobilize 0,0 50 civ     convert 50 mil to civilians at capital
  demo * 200                shorthand alias

SEE ALSO
